d. The properties of the\npassive and active state light curves can be explained in terms of clumpy\naccretion from a trapped inner accretion disc near the corotation radius,\nresulting in rectangular, flat-bottomed optical and X-ray light curves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Jul 2015 16:24:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-23"}
